content:
Administer sync features from a central location and benefit from optimized sync capabilities for an enhanced sync experience.

Centrally Administer Your Sync Experience: Get a consolidated view of relevant sync features and manage settings on the Sync Settings page. Determine usage for your users, optimize experience by downloading incremental data and setting a maximum user threshold, and trace logs using unique IDs to resolve configuration issues.

Expedite Sync Using Optimized Named Fetch Trees: Save on data volume and time taken to download data by downloading incremental REST-based named fetch trees updates.

Identify Sync Records in Logs Easily with Sync IDs: Use the unique ID assigned to each synchronization operation to improve debugging and troubleshooting, filtering and tracing sync transactions, and planning necessary actions.

Process Simultaneous Sync Request Load Efficiently: Configure the maximum number of concurrent users on the Sync Configuration tab to prevent overloading the system and maintain optimal performance when sales reps initiate sync simultaneously from their mobile devices.

Improve Support for Solving Sync Issues by Logging Extended Sync KPIs: Get better support and assistance to analyze and resolve sync configuration issues by sending sync-related KPIs to Salesforce, allowing admins to review collected KPIs and take actions to optimize sync performance.

Include CPU Calculation Time in APEX Calculation: Protect your system from Apex CPU governance limit exceptions by incorporating a buffer in the calculation of sync execution time.
title: Enhanced Sync Experience in Salesforce
